  "texts": [
    "HC2 is clearly much slower than MR-Hydra.",
    "This is at least in parts the result of the configuration and implementation of HC2.",
    "For example, TDE, a component of HC2, is not optimised using numba foot_11.",
    "Nevertheless, there is no doubt that MR-Hydra offers a good accuracy/train time trade off: it is on average as accurate as HC2 but orders of magnitude faster.",
    "If results are required very quickly or train set sizes are large, MR-Hydra would seem to be the better option."
  ],
